      <item>
        <title>Intent vs. Outcome Based Models</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Pass related models, such as pass success probability and pitch control, usually implicitly assume that a pass would precisely reach a target coordinate. However, we need to account for the fact that sometimes, and probably very often, the player may intend to pass to a particular location but may pass somewhere in the neighbourhood of that location and not exactly at that location.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://thecomeonman.github.io/IntentVsOutcome/&quot;&gt;Full post here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
